1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Taking walks and playing games when there's sunny weather

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:15,000
If there's rain, they're singing songs or reading books together

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Every day just has a way of feeling extra lucky

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
When you spend it with a friend, just like Bjorn and Bucky

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Just like Bjorn and Bucky!

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Old-fashioned food!

7
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,000
The master chef at work!

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
His ancient secret recipe

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Is a nutritious road map to yummy town!

10
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Oh, here already?

11
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Bwong, bwong, bwong, bwong!

12
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Hi there! Come on in!

13
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Hey!

14
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Yummy!

15
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Am I early Bjorn?

16
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Not at all Buck!

17
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,000
It's almost ready!

18
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,000
What did you make?

19
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Well?

20
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Pie?

21
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Well, it isn't pie, no!

22
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Then what?

23
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Cake?

24
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Not cake, no sir!

25
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Wait and see!

26
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Is it cupcakes then?

27
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,000
It's not cupcakes!

28
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,000
It's ice cream!

29
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Wrong again!

30
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Well then what?

31
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Are we even really going to have something?

32
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Behold!

33
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Smells so good, right?

34
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:21,000
This is our ancient northern recipe!

35
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:22,000
What's this stuff?

36
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Soup?

37
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Yeah!

38
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:31,000
Wise bears teach us to eat lots of food that's nutritious before the start of winter!

39
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,000
And this soup has lots of yummy things!

40
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Mushrooms, cabbage, and carrots!

41
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Just stop!

42
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,000
You said this wouldn't be some old dull lunch!

43
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,000
You promised a feast!

44
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,000
This is a feast where I'm from!

45
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,000
We call it Grand Poobot Chowder!

46
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,000
I opened a can of really special spongy mushrooms for it!

47
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Thanks a lot Bjorn!

48
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:44,000
But soup doesn't sound that good to me!

49
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
I'd rather just stick with my yummy chips here!

50
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,000
I'm not that hungry!

51
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:51,000
If you're not really hungry, why do you keep eating all those chips then?

52
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,000
They're bad for you!

53
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Remember, when summer's over, there won't be anything like this soup!

54
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
I sleep all winter long, so summer's never over for me!

55
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,000
And then I'm hungry!

56
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,000
I'm hungry!

57
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,000
I'm hungry!

58
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,000
I'm hungry!

59
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,000
I'm hungry!

60
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,000
I'm hungry!

61
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,000
I'm hungry!

62
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,000
I'm hungry!

63
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,000
I'm hungry!

64
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,000
I'm hungry!

65
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,000
I'm hungry!

66
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,000
I'm hungry!

67
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,000
I'm hungry!

68
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,000
I'm hungry!

69
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,000
I'm hungry!

70
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,000
I'm hungry!

71
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,000
I'm hungry!

72
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,000
I'm hungry!

73
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,000
I'm hungry!

74
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,000
And no cooking required!

75
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,000
But the way we did it, back up north…

76
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Up north we did this and we did that!

77
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Your ways are so old fashioned up north with your fungus weed soup or whatever!

78
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,000
But this is modern food!

79
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:33,000
It was made in a factory with machines and smart technology!

80
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Well, if you don't like the kind of food that I make, then the next time you can cook!

81
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Come on Bjorn!

82
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Don't be upset!

83
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Hey!

84
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Listen!

85
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,000
I'll make something that's delicious for you!

86
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,000
So good your taste buds will explode!

87
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Genius time!

88
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
I'll invent a recipe that's totally new!

89
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:55,000
It'll be… foodtastic!

90
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Behold!

91
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,000
Nah, not good enough yet!

92
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,000
What else could I use?

93
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Ha!

94
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Gotta use gummy bears!

95
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Nice!

96
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Look so yummy!

97
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Oh!

98
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,000
I love hot dogs too!

99
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Ooh!

100
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
And meringue!

101
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Chocolate of course!

102
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,000
Burgers!

103
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,000
Wait!

104
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Wiener burgers!

105
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Gingerbread!

106
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,000
Cookies!

107
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,000
Yeah!

108
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Now lots of mayonnaise on top!

109
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,000
Ice cream!

110
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,000
And cupcakes!

111
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,000
It's so beautiful!

112
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,000
Super McDuper!

113
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:32,000
Now that is what I call a real beast!

114
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:35,000
I better get Bjorn over here before the ice cream melts!

115
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Ha ha!

116
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Bjorn, you are going to flip!

117
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Prepare yourself!

118
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
You are about to be truly amazed!

119
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Oh, wow!

120
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Cool sculpture, Bucky!

121
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
It isn't a sculpture at all!

122
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
It's a super McDuper dish that I invented!

123
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
It sure is taller than your regular food!

124
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,000
It had to be big enough to fit all the flavor!

125
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Now then!

126
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Borg a train to yummy town!

127
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Eat that stuff?

128
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,000
You really serious?

129
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Trust me, you're going to be begging for seconds, thirds, tenths!

130
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Ew!

131
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Disgusting!

132
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,000
What?

133
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,000
Disgusting?

134
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Impossible!

135
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Gross, right?

136
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,000
You don't look so good, Buck!

137
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,000
You all right over there?

138
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,000
I'm just fine!

139
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,000
I've never had yummier food!

140
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,000
It's really nutritious as well!

141
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Bucky?

142
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Junk food avalanche!

143
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Bucky, run!

144
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
No!

145
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:40,000
My beautiful recipe!

146
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Lost!

147
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Gone forever!

148
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,000
The food-manity!

149
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Why?

150
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,000
And I just realized I'm starving.

151
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,000
It's all right, Bucky.

152
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
We'll clean the whole mess up.

153
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,000
And when we're done, you can reconstruct your dish.

154
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Your modern and high-tech, disgusting, horrible, awful dish.

155
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Uh, Bjorn, know what?

156
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Let's head to your house.

157
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,000
You've got some soup left over there, s-

158
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Ah!

159
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Try not to lick the paint off the bowl.

160
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Yeah!

161
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Grand Poobot chowder!

162
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:17,000
They should call it Bucky's Bottomless Belly Bisque.

163
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,000
That is literally your tenth helping.

164
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Can I have elevenths?

165
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,000
Please?

166
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Please?

167
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Please?

